+# Examples: `fix mc/sites` + `compute sites/voronoi`
+
+Two small, fast examples (each runs in well under a second, serial or on 4 ranks) that
+demonstrate site-resolved lattice-gas Monte Carlo on a Voronoi-derived interstitial-site
+catalogue. For the full command semantics and the science, see the manual pages
+[`fix mc/sites`](../../../doc/src/fix_mc_sites.rst) and
+[`compute sites/voronoi`](../../../doc/src/compute_sites_voronoi.rst). During the pre-PR
+review, the build instructions and project context are in the MC-SITES-LAMMPS project
+README that accompanies this `feature/mc-sites` branch.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+A LAMMPS binary built with the `MC` and `VORONOI` packages (on the GRACE fork, also
+`ML-PACE` — see the build gotcha in the root README). Below, `lmp` is that binary.
+
+```bash
+# serial
+lmp -in in.mc_sites.langmuir
+# parallel
+mpirun -np 4 lmp -in in.mc_sites.langmuir
+```
+
+Reference logs are committed next to each input
+(`log.11Feb2026.mc_sites.*.appleclang.{1,4}`) so you can diff your run against a known-good
+result.
+
+---
+
+## Example 1 — `in.mc_sites.langmuir` (start here)
+
+**What it is.** The cleanest possible correctness check: a non-interacting lattice gas. An
+fcc host (Ni-mass atoms, `pair_style zero` so there are *no* interactions) with the dynamic
+`sites/voronoi` catalogue windowed by `rmin 1.6` to select exactly the octahedral
+interstitial sites. Grand-canonical trials run at chemical potential μ = 0.
+
+**What to expect.** With no interactions, ΔU = 0 for every trial, so each site is occupied
+independently with probability θ = 1 / (1 + e^(−μ/kT)). At **μ = 0 this is exactly
+θ = 0.5.** Watch the `f_MC[6]` column (instantaneous site concentration) converge to 0.5 as
+the run proceeds:
+
+```
+thermo_style custom step atoms f_MC[4] f_MC[5] f_MC[6] f_MC[7]
+#                              N_spec  M       theta   accept
+```
+
+The occupancy fluctuates around 0.5; over the run it should average to 0.5 within a couple
+of percent. Change `mu 0.0` to `mu 0.04` or `mu -0.04` and θ should shift up/down along the
+analytic Langmuir isotherm (the full isotherm is checked in `tests/test_8_2_langmuir.py`).
+
+**Key commands.**
+
+```
+compute SITES all sites/voronoi rmerge 0.3 rmin 1.6 rmax 2.0
+fix     MC    all mc/sites 1 20 2 29494 300.0 sites c_SITES mode gc mu 0.0
+#                          |  |  |  |     |     |     |            |
+#                    Nevery |  |  seed   T(K)  sites= the compute  lattice-gas mu (eV)
+#                       Ntrials |
+#                          MC species atom type
+```
+
+---
+
+## Example 2 — `in.mc_sites.dynamic` (hybrid MD/MC)
+
+**What it is.** The realistic use case: MC coupled to running MD. An `lj/cut` fcc host is
+thermostatted at 30 K with `fix nvt`; every 10 MD steps one MC block of 20 grand-canonical
+trials runs on the **current** Voronoi-vertex catalogue, so the site list follows the
+thermal displacements of the host from step to step.
+
+**What to expect.** A stable hybrid run: finite total energy, no lost atoms, temperature
+bounded, and a populated catalogue that is rebuilt every block from the instantaneous
+geometry. Because the host now *interacts* with the inserted species (attractive `lj`
+cross-term), the occupancy at a given μ sits higher than the non-interacting μ = 0 value —
+this is the physics the method is for. `f_MC[7]` (acceptance ratio) stays healthy because
+insertions are proposed only at real interstitial sites.
+
+```
+fix INT all nvt temp 30.0 30.0 0.05
+fix MC  all mc/sites 10 20 2 62717 300.0 sites c_SITES mode gc mu -0.15
+```
+
+Note the two temperatures are independent and intentional: 30 K is the *MD* host
+temperature, 300 K is the *MC* sampling temperature in the acceptance rule.
+
+---
+
+## Reading the `fix mc/sites` output vector
+
+The fix exposes a global vector of length 8 (all values intensive), accessible as
+`f_ID[i]`:
+
+| i | quantity |
+|---|---|
+| 1 | trial attempts (this run) |
+| 2 | accepted insertions |
+| 3 | accepted deletions |
+| 4 | current number of species atoms in the catalogue |
+| 5 | catalogue size M (empty + occupied) |
+| 6 | instantaneous site concentration = (4)/(5) |
+| 7 | overall acceptance ratio |
+| 8 | skipped `source`-mode insertions |
+
+For the Langmuir check the quantity of interest is **`f_MC[6]` → 0.5**. For source-mode
+(irradiation) runs, `f_MC[8]` counts insertions skipped because the catalogue was exhausted
+or a site failed the `overlap_cutoff` guard.
+
+---
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+- **"accepted site clearance exceeds the ghost cutoff" warning** from the compute: a site's
+  empty sphere is larger than the communication cutoff, so its tessellation may be
+  incomplete. Increase the ghost cutoff with `comm_modify cutoff <r>` or tighten `rmax`.
+- **Occupancy stuck at 0 or 1:** check the sign/magnitude of `mu` and that `rmin/rmax`
+  actually select sites (the global scalar `c_SITES` is the site count; dump it if unsure).
+- **Build fails with `pair_pace.h not found`:** that is the fork's `MC`→`ML-PACE` coupling,
+  not this example — add `-D PKG_ML-PACE=on -D NO_GRACE_TF=1` (see the root README).
+- **Serial vs parallel differ:** small statistical differences are expected (different RNG
+  streams per rank); the isotherm mean must still match. Determinism is checked in
+  `tests/test_8_9_parallel.py`.
